{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Instead of relying on traditional commonsense knowledge bases, we utilize LLMs as a knowledge resource to generate implicit knowledge.",
    "This generative approach effectively addresses the sparsity problem commonly associated with traditional commonsense knowledge base [25][26][27], thereby circumventing the risk of no-hit issues.",
    "We then integrate the generated implicit knowledge \"explicitly\" with the false statement and create an augmented prompt as input for LLMs.",
    "By constructing the implicit knowledge-augmented prompt, TIP provides the LLMs with a richer and more contextually nuanced input.",
    "This enriched input enables the LLMs to reason through the inconsistency between the commonsense knowledge and the nonsensical statement, generating explanations that correct the nonsensical statement and clarify the underlying commonsense principles.To validate the effectiveness of the TIP framework, we conducted extensive experiments on two datasets used to evaluate commonsense explanation generation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
